title: Readout of National Security Advisor Jake Sullivanâ€™s Meeting with President-elect Javier Milei of Argentina | The White House
content: National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan met today with President-elect Javier Milei of Argentina to discuss the importance of continuing to build on the strong relationship between the United States and Argentina on economic issues, and on shared priorities such as investing in technology and clean energy, advocating for human rights, and standing up for democracies around the world. National Security Advisor Sullivan congratulated President-elect Milei on his election victory and committed to continued close cooperation between our two countries.
